1
00:00:10,041 --> 00:00:12,541
[MAN A] Where's our room?
This place is huge!

2
00:00:12,625 --> 00:00:14,750
[WOMAN A giggles] We have
to have a party here!

3
00:00:14,833 --> 00:00:17,333
[MAN A chuckles]

4
00:00:24,333 --> 00:00:26,208
[AKECHI]
Where was it?

5
00:00:31,041 --> 00:00:33,083
[gunshot]

6
00:00:36,166 --> 00:00:41,250
[AKECHI] Where did
I finally... let it go?

7
00:00:43,458 --> 00:00:47,541
[AKECHI]
Where did I give in? Accept it?

8
00:00:50,500 --> 00:00:55,291
[AKECHI]
Him and his policy.

9
00:00:56,958 --> 00:01:00,208
[gasps]

10
00:01:00,291 --> 00:01:02,583
That was lovely.

11
00:01:32,083 --> 00:01:34,250
[TWENTY-FACES]
You really are...

12
00:01:38,500 --> 00:01:41,708
...the very best kind of evil.

13
00:01:48,458 --> 00:01:53,458
♪

14
00:03:21,375 --> 00:03:22,916
[TWENTY-FACES]
Akechi!

15
00:03:23,000 --> 00:03:24,416
[AKECHI]
Hm?

16
00:03:24,500 --> 00:03:26,541
We'll be heading out soon!

17
00:03:28,375 --> 00:03:29,958
[AKECHI sighs]

18
00:03:42,791 --> 00:03:44,375
[TWENTY-FACES]
Crazy.

19
00:03:44,458 --> 00:03:47,416
I didn't think we'd have
traveled this far.

20
00:03:47,500 --> 00:03:50,166
We keep going deeper
and deeper still.

21
00:03:50,250 --> 00:03:53,333
Running headlong
into certain danger.

22
00:03:53,416 --> 00:03:56,875
It's exciting. What a life!

23
00:03:56,958 --> 00:03:58,000
Right.

24
00:03:58,083 --> 00:04:02,750
[gasps]
Aren't you thrilled?

25
00:04:02,833 --> 00:04:04,166
[AKECHI grunts]

26
00:04:04,250 --> 00:04:07,125
[TWENTY-FACES] Are you not
satisfied by this anymore?

27
00:04:07,208 --> 00:04:09,333
[AKECHI]
Huh?

28
00:04:09,416 --> 00:04:12,166
[AKECHI] When chaos
is your daily bread...

29
00:04:16,000 --> 00:04:19,750
[AKECHI] ...even extraordinary
days can bore you to tears.

30
00:04:25,083 --> 00:04:26,000
[AKECHI gasps]

31
00:04:26,083 --> 00:04:29,208
[TWENTY-FACES gasps]
What is it?

32
00:04:37,250 --> 00:04:40,875
[AKECHI] Fumiyo introduced
herself as a reporter.

33
00:04:40,958 --> 00:04:42,458
[AKECHI grunts]

34
00:04:48,166 --> 00:04:52,166
[AKECHI] Every aspect of my
daily life shook her world;

35
00:04:52,250 --> 00:04:53,958
broke her heart.

36
00:04:56,208 --> 00:04:59,708
[AKECHI] Her reactions
seemed so new. Refreshing.

37
00:04:59,791 --> 00:05:02,500
[gasps, giggles]

38
00:05:02,583 --> 00:05:06,041
[AKECHI] I became attracted
to how "normal" she was.

39
00:05:06,125 --> 00:05:09,541
Hey, Fumiyo! Is this
what you wanted?

40
00:05:09,625 --> 00:05:12,291
[FUMIYO gasps]
You found it!

41
00:05:13,750 --> 00:05:16,708
You're the best.
Seriously, thanks so much!

42
00:05:18,500 --> 00:05:22,208
So, you were interested.
Can't say I blame you.

43
00:05:22,291 --> 00:05:24,416
[TWENTY-FACES]
Huh?

44
00:05:24,500 --> 00:05:26,291
[AKECHI]
That's for Fumiyo, right?

45
00:05:26,375 --> 00:05:29,958
Don't be shy. It's nice of you.

46
00:05:30,041 --> 00:05:31,375
[chuckles]

47
00:05:31,458 --> 00:05:32,833
What's funny?

48
00:05:32,916 --> 00:05:35,125
I have no interest in being
someone's romantic rival,

49
00:05:35,208 --> 00:05:37,250
believe me.

50
00:05:37,333 --> 00:05:40,208
What? What are
you talkin' about?

51
00:05:40,291 --> 00:05:43,833
[TWENTY-FACES chuckles]
You're smart. Figure it out.

52
00:05:43,916 --> 00:05:46,000
I have all I've ever needed.

53
00:05:46,083 --> 00:05:47,458
[AKECHI gasps]

54
00:05:48,583 --> 00:05:51,250
[TWENTY-FACES]
Find us a thrill.

55
00:05:51,333 --> 00:05:53,375
That's your gift, after all.

56
00:05:53,458 --> 00:05:57,125
[grunts]

57
00:05:57,208 --> 00:05:58,833
[KATSUTA]
He's been here for five days?

58
00:05:58,916 --> 00:06:01,666
[NORO] 
Been asleep the whole time, too.

59
00:06:01,750 --> 00:06:03,416
[KATSUTA]
What are you gonna do now?

60
00:06:03,500 --> 00:06:04,916
I'm thinking.

61
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:07,666
Don't waste the brain cells.
There's nothing you can do.

62
00:06:07,750 --> 00:06:09,916
Unless I'm mistaken,
the Boy Detective's Club

63
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:11,541
has gone the way of
the Dodo, right?

64
00:06:11,625 --> 00:06:13,666
[YAMANE]
Huh?! But I just joined!

65
00:06:13,750 --> 00:06:16,041
[NORO] That sure came out
of the blue, huh, Inoue?

66
00:06:16,125 --> 00:06:18,791
It's not like any of us
knew about it before hand.

67
00:06:18,875 --> 00:06:20,291
Noro.

68
00:06:20,375 --> 00:06:22,000
[NORO] Katsuta, please tell
Inoue that I'm not speaking

69
00:06:22,083 --> 00:06:23,791
to him anymore.

70
00:06:23,875 --> 00:06:26,666
Aw, you made the little
homebody angry.

71
00:06:26,750 --> 00:06:29,833
Are you here to do anything
besides annoy us?

72
00:06:29,916 --> 00:06:31,208
[OHTOMO]
To collect my fee.

73
00:06:31,291 --> 00:06:33,375
The tools I made
for you were pricey.

74
00:06:33,458 --> 00:06:34,791
[NORO sighs]

75
00:06:34,875 --> 00:06:36,875
Think you could pick a better
time to be a cheapskate?

76
00:06:36,958 --> 00:06:38,708
[OHTOMO] This is your
chance to stop adhering

77
00:06:38,791 --> 00:06:40,291
to that jerk's every whim.

78
00:06:40,375 --> 00:06:41,208
'Scuse me?

79
00:06:41,291 --> 00:06:42,083
[YAMANE gasps]

80
00:06:42,166 --> 00:06:44,250
Look, don't get me wrong here.

81
00:06:44,333 --> 00:06:48,166
I like you guys, but your boss
gave me a bad vibe from day one.

82
00:06:48,250 --> 00:06:49,333
Ease up, man.

83
00:06:49,416 --> 00:06:51,250
[OHTOMO] I mean,
how shady can the guy be?

84
00:06:51,333 --> 00:06:53,583
Gathering a bunch of
teenagers and an owl

85
00:06:53,666 --> 00:06:55,541
under his roof is
majorly creepy.

86
00:06:55,625 --> 00:06:57,791
I'm getting tired
of your mouth!

87
00:06:57,875 --> 00:07:01,750
You think I care? You're just
afraid of losing your place.

88
00:07:01,833 --> 00:07:02,791
Why, you.

89
00:07:02,875 --> 00:07:04,458
Knock it off.
This isn't helping!

90
00:07:04,541 --> 00:07:08,291
[sniffs, gasps]

91
00:07:10,041 --> 00:07:12,166
--[KATSUTA gasps]
--[NORO] Katusda! Get back!

92
00:07:14,541 --> 00:07:16,666
[ALL gasp]

93
00:07:18,041 --> 00:07:20,458
[exhales]

94
00:07:20,541 --> 00:07:21,458
Huh?

95
00:07:21,541 --> 00:07:22,916
Wow...

96
00:07:23,000 --> 00:07:25,041
[NORO]
His power's getting desperate.

97
00:07:25,125 --> 00:07:29,750
It's absorbing everything it
can in order to keep him alive.

98
00:07:29,833 --> 00:07:32,291
Koba must really want to die.

99
00:07:39,291 --> 00:07:43,083
[AKECHI] Goodbyes always
come as if they're meant to.

100
00:07:44,958 --> 00:07:47,250
[TWENTY-FACES] Fumiyo's going
back home already?

101
00:07:47,333 --> 00:07:49,250
[AKECHI] She's got all
the material she needed.

102
00:07:49,333 --> 00:07:50,750
You doing okay?

103
00:07:50,833 --> 00:07:53,333
Yeah. it's for
the best, I think.

104
00:07:53,416 --> 00:07:56,625
If she stayed here, we'd only
end up get her killed.

105
00:07:56,708 --> 00:07:58,375
[TWENTY-FACES]
Huh?

106
00:07:58,458 --> 00:08:02,375
The life of a thrill seeker
isn't for her. Just us freaks.

107
00:08:02,458 --> 00:08:05,125
[TWENTY-FACES gasps]

108
00:08:15,500 --> 00:08:16,958
[TWENTY-FACES]
Heh.

109
00:08:20,750 --> 00:08:23,583
Ready to go whenever
you are, Fumiyo.

110
00:08:25,875 --> 00:08:27,375
For you.

111
00:08:39,208 --> 00:08:41,041
[AKECHI grunts]

112
00:08:43,791 --> 00:08:45,541
[TWENTY-FACES grunts]

113
00:08:45,625 --> 00:08:47,000
[gasps]

114
00:08:53,625 --> 00:08:54,500
[TWENTY-FACES]
Goodbye.

115
00:08:54,583 --> 00:08:56,375
[FUMIYO gasps]

116
00:09:02,500 --> 00:09:05,458
[AKECHI gasps]

117
00:09:05,541 --> 00:09:06,708
Stop!

118
00:09:06,791 --> 00:09:08,375
[FUMIYO gasps]

119
00:09:09,750 --> 00:09:12,750
Go with her. It's for the best.

120
00:09:12,833 --> 00:09:15,083
[AKECHI]
Huh?

121
00:09:15,166 --> 00:09:18,541
[TWENTY-FACES] I can't
satisfy you anymore, Akechi.

122
00:09:18,625 --> 00:09:20,666
[AKECHI gasps]

123
00:09:20,750 --> 00:09:22,208
[TWENTY-FACES]
Fumiyo,

124
00:09:22,291 --> 00:09:25,666
Make sure his life is
full of thrills for me.

125
00:09:28,625 --> 00:09:30,833
[AKECHI]
After all these years.

126
00:09:30,916 --> 00:09:33,791
The scent of those
flowers linger.

127
00:09:45,166 --> 00:09:46,583
[bell rings]

128
00:09:46,666 --> 00:09:48,333
[WOMAN CLIENT]
Excuse me.

129
00:09:48,416 --> 00:09:52,333
Table for one, ma'am?
Sit anywhere you like.

130
00:09:52,416 --> 00:09:55,458
Actually. I'm looking
for a detective?

131
00:09:55,541 --> 00:09:59,125
[AKECHI] Hm. Then you're
in the right place.

132
00:09:59,208 --> 00:10:02,375
Sorry it was such
a hassle to find.

133
00:10:02,458 --> 00:10:05,708
So, what's the job?
It'll be on the house.

134
00:10:05,791 --> 00:10:07,125
[WOMAN CLIENT]
What?

135
00:10:07,208 --> 00:10:10,791
[AKECHI] Special occasion.
You're our first customer.

136
00:10:10,875 --> 00:10:13,666
[AKECHI] Fumiyo's the one
who suggested it to me.

137
00:10:13,750 --> 00:10:16,291
I'd never held a job longer
than a month before,

138
00:10:16,375 --> 00:10:19,375
but investigative
work came naturally.

139
00:10:22,708 --> 00:10:27,250
[AKECHI] Sup? They need me down
at the station? Yeah, sure.

140
00:10:27,333 --> 00:10:30,083
As long as they can give me a
lift in a squad car, that is.

141
00:10:30,166 --> 00:10:31,750
[AKECHI chuckles]

142
00:10:33,958 --> 00:10:37,125
[AKECHI] It was just what I
needed to forget all the pain.

143
00:10:38,916 --> 00:10:44,875
[AKECHI] My past, my fathers,
and most of all, him.

144
00:10:44,958 --> 00:10:46,750
Don't go too far.

145
00:10:46,833 --> 00:10:48,208
Uh...

146
00:10:51,333 --> 00:10:52,708
[AKECHI]
Hm.

147
00:10:53,875 --> 00:10:57,000
[AKECHI]
The Fiend with twenty faces?

148
00:11:01,583 --> 00:11:03,500
Oh, my head.

149
00:11:07,208 --> 00:11:10,833
[DRUNK MAN groans]
Damn, why did I drink so--

150
00:11:10,916 --> 00:11:11,500
[DRUNK MAN screams]

151
00:11:11,583 --> 00:11:14,458
[CROWD screams]

152
00:11:14,541 --> 00:11:16,625
[NAMIKOSHI]
That's the eighth one.

153
00:11:16,708 --> 00:11:18,750
What's this
"Twenty-Faces" after?

154
00:11:18,833 --> 00:11:20,125
[NAMIKOSHI]
Who knows?

155
00:11:20,208 --> 00:11:22,958
Fortunately, there haven't
been any victims, yet.

156
00:11:23,041 --> 00:11:26,916
We need to nab him
before that changes.

157
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:29,208
That's why you leaked his
name to the press, right?.

158
00:11:29,291 --> 00:11:32,500
You sure that was a good idea?
It could backfire on you.

159
00:11:32,583 --> 00:11:35,416
I'm retiring in half a month,
I couldn't care less.

160
00:11:35,500 --> 00:11:38,666
[AKECHI] Hmph. Jeez, no wonder
you're so stressed out.

161
00:11:38,750 --> 00:11:41,250
[NAMIKOSHI]
The usual, right?

162
00:11:41,333 --> 00:11:43,458
[AKECHI]
I understand now.

163
00:11:43,541 --> 00:11:46,375
Whether he changes
his name or his looks,

164
00:11:46,458 --> 00:11:50,041
he's still him and I'm still me.

165
00:11:50,875 --> 00:11:55,833
[phone rings]

166
00:11:57,041 --> 00:11:59,416
[AKECHI grunts]
A ninth hit?

167
00:11:59,500 --> 00:12:00,958
[NAMIKOSHI]
No, not yet.

168
00:12:01,041 --> 00:12:02,958
Then what?

169
00:12:03,041 --> 00:12:05,083
[NAMIKOSHI]
He's screwing with us.

170
00:12:11,375 --> 00:12:14,916
[TWENTY-FACES] "Tonight,
along with the ninth signal.

171
00:12:15,000 --> 00:12:18,875
I will come to partake
of the finest reward."

172
00:12:18,958 --> 00:12:21,000
Twenty-Faces.

173
00:12:24,208 --> 00:12:26,833
[AKECHI gasps]
Call Fumiyo right now!

174
00:12:26,916 --> 00:12:27,333
[NAMIKOSHI]
Huh?

175
00:12:27,416 --> 00:12:28,166
Do it!

176
00:12:28,250 --> 00:12:30,458
[NAMIKOSHI]
Fine.

177
00:12:30,541 --> 00:12:32,291
[AKECHI gasps]

178
00:12:34,375 --> 00:12:35,625
[AKECHI grunts]

179
00:12:35,708 --> 00:12:36,833
[NAMIKOSHI]
Fumiyo?

180
00:12:36,916 --> 00:12:37,958
Did she answer?

181
00:12:38,041 --> 00:12:38,750
Uh-huh.

182
00:12:38,833 --> 00:12:40,208
Is she still at the shop?

183
00:12:40,291 --> 00:12:41,625
I think so.

184
00:12:41,708 --> 00:12:43,708
[AKECHI] Get over
there and protect her!

185
00:12:43,791 --> 00:12:46,291
Hey! You gonna tell
me what's going on?

186
00:12:46,375 --> 00:12:47,708
No, course not.

187
00:12:47,791 --> 00:12:51,000
Oh, sorry it's nothing,
I'm just talking to myself.

188
00:12:53,375 --> 00:12:54,833
[gasps]

189
00:13:03,958 --> 00:13:05,958
[AKECHI]
Unbelievable.

190
00:13:11,583 --> 00:13:14,750
Aren't you gonna tag along?

191
00:13:14,833 --> 00:13:17,291
Sorry, I can't do that.

192
00:13:17,375 --> 00:13:18,541
[AKECHI grunts]

193
00:13:18,625 --> 00:13:20,333
[FUMIYO giggles]

194
00:13:22,958 --> 00:13:27,333
[AKECHI] That look in his eyes.
I should have recognized it.

195
00:13:27,416 --> 00:13:28,791
But...

196
00:13:37,583 --> 00:13:39,875
--[phone rings]
--[AKECHI gasps]

197
00:13:43,375 --> 00:13:44,916
[AKECHI grunts]

198
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:47,000
[TWENTY-FACES]
Aren't you going to answer that?

199
00:13:47,083 --> 00:13:49,458
[gasps]

200
00:13:49,541 --> 00:13:54,500
[ringing continues]

201
00:14:00,708 --> 00:14:03,958
[TWENTY-FACES]
It's been a long time.

202
00:14:04,041 --> 00:14:07,208
[AKECHI gasps]

203
00:14:07,291 --> 00:14:09,041
[TWENTY-FACES]
Akechi.

204
00:14:27,875 --> 00:14:33,416
[AKECHI groans]

205
00:14:33,500 --> 00:14:37,291
[AKECHI]
Fumiyo? Fumiyo!

206
00:14:39,041 --> 00:14:40,791
[AKECHI gasps]

207
00:14:40,875 --> 00:14:43,916
[TWENTY-FACES]
What a lovely expression.

208
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:48,291
[AKECHI gasps]
It was you. All of it.

209
00:14:49,916 --> 00:14:52,916
[TWENTY-FACES]
Last time I saw it...

210
00:14:53,000 --> 00:14:55,583
...was the day you took my life.

211
00:14:57,541 --> 00:15:00,750
Fumiyo...! Fumiyo!

212
00:15:00,833 --> 00:15:01,791
[TWENTY-FACES]
Akechi!

213
00:15:01,875 --> 00:15:04,041
[AKECHI gasps]

214
00:15:04,125 --> 00:15:07,083
[AKECHI] Huh? What are
you doing out here?

215
00:15:07,166 --> 00:15:08,875
[TWENTY-FACES] I heard over
the wireless that your ride

216
00:15:08,958 --> 00:15:10,916
went up in smoke.

217
00:15:12,708 --> 00:15:14,416
Where's Fumiyo?

218
00:15:16,000 --> 00:15:19,250
[AKECHI exhales]
I don't know.

219
00:15:19,333 --> 00:15:21,875
Stop looking pathetic
and find her!

220
00:15:23,166 --> 00:15:24,458
[TWENTY-FACES]
I'll help.

221
00:15:24,541 --> 00:15:27,458
There should be a few
mountain shacks around here.

222
00:15:27,541 --> 00:15:28,708
[AKECHI gasps]

223
00:15:28,791 --> 00:15:31,583
[AKECHI grunts]

224
00:15:31,666 --> 00:15:33,291
[TWENTY-FACES]
Akechi?

225
00:15:34,583 --> 00:15:39,666
[AKECHI] Those flowers.
The scent is all over you!

226
00:15:39,750 --> 00:15:41,458
You did this!

227
00:15:43,125 --> 00:15:44,791
--[TWENTY-FACES chuckles]
--[phone rings]

228
00:15:46,250 --> 00:15:51,000
Detective Namikoshi is
probably at your house by now.

229
00:15:51,083 --> 00:15:53,583
I wouldn't keep him waiting.

230
00:15:54,666 --> 00:15:58,708
Bastard! What'd you
do with Fumiyo?

231
00:15:59,916 --> 00:16:02,333
What do you mean, Akechi?

232
00:16:02,416 --> 00:16:04,291
I did nothing.

233
00:16:04,375 --> 00:16:06,833
Don't look at me like that!

234
00:16:09,375 --> 00:16:13,791
[AKECHI] What are you thinking?
Which face is the real you?

235
00:16:15,625 --> 00:16:19,291
[TWENTY-FACES]
My dear. That's your choice.

236
00:16:19,375 --> 00:16:21,666
Which one do you like?

237
00:16:21,750 --> 00:16:23,541
Don't joke around!

238
00:16:23,625 --> 00:16:26,458
Did you enjoy
this thrill, Akechi?

239
00:16:28,166 --> 00:16:31,041
The next one will
be even better.

240
00:16:31,125 --> 00:16:32,666
[AKECHI grunts]

241
00:16:33,666 --> 00:16:35,083
[gasps]

242
00:16:40,416 --> 00:16:42,458
Fumiyo?

243
00:16:47,500 --> 00:16:51,416
[AKECHI] Damn you!
What did you do to her?

244
00:16:51,500 --> 00:16:53,041
[TWENTY-FACES]
Hm.

245
00:16:56,291 --> 00:16:57,958
[AKECHI gasps]

246
00:17:00,458 --> 00:17:02,666
I shared something
precious with her.

247
00:17:02,750 --> 00:17:06,125
My gift. Just for you.

248
00:17:06,208 --> 00:17:09,208
What's that mean? Tell me!

249
00:17:10,750 --> 00:17:12,875
These lips can charm.

250
00:17:12,958 --> 00:17:16,583
Anyone they touch
bends to my will.

251
00:17:16,666 --> 00:17:18,500
[grunts]

252
00:17:18,583 --> 00:17:22,541
[TWENTY-FACES] But you don't
have time to worry about that.

253
00:17:22,625 --> 00:17:26,000
Fumiyo needs your
undivided attention.

254
00:17:27,500 --> 00:17:31,041
[TWENTY-FACES] I wonder who
was behind those explosions?

255
00:17:31,125 --> 00:17:33,500
Maybe you should ask her.

256
00:17:37,458 --> 00:17:40,458
[gasps]

257
00:17:40,541 --> 00:17:42,083
[FUMIYO]
Thrills.

258
00:17:43,875 --> 00:17:47,375
That's my only purpose.
To make them for you.

259
00:17:50,375 --> 00:17:54,583
[AKECHI]
Fumiyo, please. Drop them!

260
00:17:54,666 --> 00:17:58,083
You don't have to
do what he says!

261
00:17:58,166 --> 00:17:59,583
I do.

262
00:18:04,875 --> 00:18:06,750
[AKECHI]
Stop!

263
00:18:10,625 --> 00:18:14,583
I'm begging you!

264
00:18:16,458 --> 00:18:21,125
So... having fun yet?

265
00:18:21,208 --> 00:18:22,916
[FUMIYO giggles]

266
00:18:23,000 --> 00:18:25,291
[gunshot]

267
00:18:58,375 --> 00:19:03,333
[phone rings]

268
00:19:05,750 --> 00:19:08,875
Is this the Akechi
Investigation firm?

269
00:19:08,958 --> 00:19:11,333
What do you want?

270
00:19:11,416 --> 00:19:13,625
[NAKAMURA] I'm Detective
Namikoshi's successor.

271
00:19:13,708 --> 00:19:15,750
My name's Nakamura.

272
00:19:15,833 --> 00:19:18,125
[AKECHI]
Same question.

273
00:19:18,208 --> 00:19:21,916
[NAKAMURA] We got another
warning note from Twenty-Faces.

274
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:24,458
I'd like you to assist
in apprehending him.

275
00:19:24,541 --> 00:19:26,458
[AKECHI]
Hmph.

276
00:19:26,541 --> 00:19:28,083
[AKECHI]
Is this a joke?

277
00:19:28,166 --> 00:19:30,333
The only reason he's
still causing problems is

278
00:19:30,416 --> 00:19:33,958
because you failed to
catch him. So fix it.

279
00:19:34,041 --> 00:19:36,458
I'll wait outside
for five minutes.

280
00:19:40,791 --> 00:19:43,041
[sighs]

281
00:19:44,833 --> 00:19:48,708
[AKECHI]
Where did I let it all go?

282
00:19:48,791 --> 00:19:52,083
Where'd I give in and accept it?

283
00:19:55,833 --> 00:19:59,625
[AKECHI]
Him and his policy.

284
00:20:18,208 --> 00:20:23,666
[AKECHI] If I'm sure
of anything... it's this.

285
00:20:26,208 --> 00:20:30,583
[AKECHI] I used those kids,
every one of them.

286
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:34,000
[AKECHI]
I saved them.

287
00:20:34,083 --> 00:20:37,541
Gave 'em friends and
a place to belong...

288
00:20:37,625 --> 00:20:40,416
...or at least I pretended to.

289
00:20:40,500 --> 00:20:42,958
[PASSERBY]
Life's a thrill, ain't it, boy?

290
00:20:43,041 --> 00:20:44,458
[AKECHI gasps]

291
00:20:44,541 --> 00:20:46,250
[PASSERBY gasps, grunts]

292
00:20:46,333 --> 00:20:48,916
[AKECHI] What I really wanted
was a place for myself.

293
00:20:49,000 --> 00:20:52,250
To feel like a decent person.
The thrill-seeker in me was

294
00:20:52,333 --> 00:20:54,833
searching for a just cause
to use as an excuse.

295
00:20:54,916 --> 00:20:56,416
What the hell is
your problem?

296
00:20:56,500 --> 00:20:57,708
[PASSERBY gasps]

297
00:20:57,791 --> 00:21:01,166
[AKECHI] It's you, right?
I know it's you!

298
00:21:01,250 --> 00:21:03,000
You can't fool me!

299
00:21:03,083 --> 00:21:06,875
[AKECHI] But I couldn't deny
what he'd been saying anymore.

300
00:21:06,958 --> 00:21:11,833
Why only me? I don't
deserve this! Damn it!

301
00:21:12,375 --> 00:21:13,916
[gasps]

302
00:21:14,000 --> 00:21:17,875
[PASSERBY gasps]

303
00:21:17,958 --> 00:21:20,333
[AKECHI grunts]

304
00:21:20,416 --> 00:21:22,916
[AKECHI]
I am...

305
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:25,583
...irredeemably evil.

306
00:21:26,500 --> 00:21:31,458
♪

307
00:23:03,666 --> 00:23:08,625
[YOSHIO gasps]

308
00:23:12,916 --> 00:23:15,000
What the hell was that?

309
00:23:40,666 --> 00:23:43,041
[TWELVE-FACES]
"Cycle of Malice."

